Job Summary: 
Nuance is looking to hire a  Financial Analyst  to work on our Enterprise Project Office (EPO) Team out of our Burlington, MA facility once we return to our offices some time in 2021. This person will work closely with our Finance/FP&A group. They will be responsible for the creation, accuracy and timeliness of critical information needed to support our Global team in the successful implementation of our Healthcare products and services. This role does not have an option to work remotely long term. 
Responsibilities: 
This role will be involved in a variety of critical areas of our implementation process that include but may not limited to the following: 
Revenue Forecasting 
Utilization reporting 
Bookings to revenue analysis 
Backlog reporting and analysis 
Close working relationship with FP&A 
Analysis of partner relationship 
Budget analysis and monitoring 
Qualifications: 
2 or more years experience in FP&A, Finance or similar Business Analyst role 
Education - Bachelors in Finance 
Required Experience: 
Highly proficient with Excel and MS Office Applications 
Experience in revenue forecasting and analysis 
Experience building cross functional relationships 
Positive and proactive attitude and willing to conquer any opportunity 
Desired Experience: 
Experience with Salesforce and FinancialForce 
 
Additional Information:
 
Nuance offers a compelling and rewarding work environment. We offer market competitive salaries, bonus, equity, benefits, meaningful growth and development opportunities and a casual yet technically challenging work environment. Join our dynamic, entrepreneurial team and become part of our continuing success. 
